    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n226" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ά̄-θάνατος</span></b>  (the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ᾶ</span> is a necessity of the dactylic rhythm):
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">deathless, immortal;</span> also as subst., opp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βροτοί, θνητοί, ἄνδρες</span>; said of
          ‘imperishable’ possessions of the gods, <i><span class="en">Od.
            4.79</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 2.447</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἀ̄θάνατον κακόν</span> (Charybdis), <i><span class="en">Od. 12.118</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
